We have created a space blueprint that contains many templates. These templates are changed several times each year to accommodate new needs. This request is to be able to set these templates in Confluence, like the Global templates, but be able to consume them in the blueprint configuration. This allows non-developers to update the templates without developer's intervention and without needing a plugin redeployment. This request applies to space and page blueprints. 

It is important to state that we do not want to have these templates made available as global templates but be made available to and be consumed by a blueprint.

