Currently there is no ability to modify page layout using a Connect add-on. For example, if I wanted to modify the user profile page to include additional metadata about a user, it is not possible.

When a velocity template is rendered, it modifies the template in an annoying way. The following:

{code:html}
<div id="someContainerToBeModifiedWithJavascript"></div>
{code}

gets converted into

{code:html}
<div id="someContainerToBeModifiedWithJavascript" />
{code}

When this is rendered in the browser, the tag is perceived as an opening tag rather than both an opening and closing tag and causes the notorious "start tag with no end tag" bug chase. The workaround is to always make sure there's at least a space inside empty tags so Velocity thinks it's not empty and therefore doesn't autoclose it.

